    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1100"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1100">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Mexican Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 1, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note No. 1397,<note n="1" xml:id="d1100fn1">Not printed.</note> of the 29th
                    ultimo, in which, in compliance with instructions received by you from your
                    Government, you state that on April 25 foreign concerns operating in the
                    interior of the State of Chihuahua advised the Department of Foreign Relations
                    of Mexico that they have enough coal to last but a short time, and express the
                    opinion that if coal were imported at Ciudad Juárez and other points in the
                    State of Chihuahua from the United States the rebels <pb facs="0924" n="808"
                        xml:id="pg_808"/> might seize the fuel for the operation of their trains
                    between Chihuahua and Ciudad Juárez. You state that communication will soon be
                    cut off in that vicinity, and request, as a means of effective assistance to the
                    Federal forces of Mexico, that instructions be issued to the Northern Railway to
                    suspend all traffic between El Paso, Texas, and Ciudad Juárez, Chihuahua.</p>
                <p>The Department has given careful attention to your note under acknowledgement and
                    regrets that it can not entertain the request contained therein.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
